 "lrc": "[00:00.00]We still dance when the night gets heavy\n[00:15.36]Still sing when the sky turns gray\n[00:17.76]Hands up if your heart stays ready\n[00:19.68]Love don’t break, we find a way\n[00:23.76]Heyya, heyya\n[00:24.00]Yalla, yalla\n[00:24.96]Sawa, sawa\n[00:26.00]We rise, we stay\n[00:28.40]They only see the sand in the story\n[00:34.08]They only see the stone in the frame\n[00:35.84]But we got city lights, street drums, late nights\n[00:38.24]Millions of hearts with fire in the name\n[00:40.40]From Cairo rooftops to the river\n[00:42.72]From Alexandria out to the sea\n[00:45.20]We don’t need the world to understand us\n[00:47.44]We just need the world to breathe\n[00:49.76]Mama said keep your soul protected\n[00:52.08]Baba said keep your head up high\n[00:54.48]Even when the news gets reckless\n[00:56.72]Don’t let the fear move into your eyes\n[00:59.12]And if the whole world shakes\n[01:01.04]We put rhythm in the ground\n[01:03.36]If the dark gets loud\n[01:05.52]We make a brighter sound\n[01:06.88]We still dance when the night gets heavy\n[01:10.72]Still sing when the sky turns gray\n[01:13.12]Hands up if your heart stays ready\n[01:15.12]Love don’t break, we find a way\n[01:17.44]We still move when the drums start calling\n[01:19.92]Still shine when the lights go low\n[01:22.32]If one heart feels like falling\n[01:24.32]We lift it up and let it know\n[01:26.16]Heyya, heyya\n[01:28.08]Yalla, yalla\n[01:29.20]Sawa, sawa\n[01:31.84]We rise, we stay\n[01:32.00]Heyya, heyya\n[01:32.00]Yalla, yalla\n[01:32.56]Sawa, sawa\n[01:33.12]Love leads the way\n[01:36.24]This ain’t a postcard, this is people\n[01:38.40]This ain’t a camel in a scene\n[01:40.24]This is bass in the alley, kids in the traffic\n[01:42.88]Dreams in the dust trying to stay clean\n[01:44.96]This is gold in the voice of the aunties\n[01:47.20]This is tea when the night runs deep\n[01:49.52]This is jokes when the pressure gets ugly\n[01:51.84]This is faith when it’s hard to sleep\n[01:53.84]I see mothers holding families together\n[01:56.48]I see fathers praying under streetlight glow\n[01:58.08]I see young ones building something better\n[02:00.48]With a beat in the blood and a long way to go\n[02:03.36]When the world says break\n[02:04.56][Group] We don’t break\n[02:05.28]When the fear says bow\n[02:06.40][Group] We don’t bow\n[02:07.14]When the pain gets loud\n[02:08.08][Group] We sing now\n[02:10.16]We sing now, we sing now\n[02:13.60]We still dance when the night gets heavy\n[02:15.36]Still sing when the sky turns gray\n[02:17.84]Hands up if your heart stays ready\n[02:19.76]Love don’t break, we find a way\n[02:22.16]We still move when the drums start calling\n[02:24.56]Still shine when the lights go low\n[02:26.88]If one heart feels like falling\n[02:29.04]We lift it up and let it know\n[02:33.36]Ya Masr, ya Masr\n[02:33.92]Heartbeat in the drum\n[02:35.52]Ya Masr, ya Masr\n[02:42.58]Love for everyone\n[02:43.34]Heyya, heyya\n[02:43.86]Yalla, yalla\n[02:44.92]Sawa, sawa\n[02:47.67]We rise, we stay\n[02:50.16]No flag should be a reason for sorrow\n[02:54.64]No child should be afraid of tomorrow\n[02:58.88]From every border, every prayer\n[03:01.36]Every voice in the air\n[03:03.92]We are more than what they show you\n[03:06.00]More than war on a screen\n[03:08.24]More than pain in the headlines\n[03:10.56]More than ancient history\n[03:13.76]This is for the strong ones\n[03:15.60]The tired ones\n[03:18.24]The ones still smiling when life gets wild\n[03:22.24]This is not just pride\n[03:24.08]This is peace with a pulse\n[03:26.96]This is culture with arms open wide\n[03:30.32]So let the oud cry\n[03:32.48]Let the drum talk\n[03:33.36]Let the whole room move like the Nile walk\n[03:35.68]If your heart hurts\n[03:37.12]Bring it close\n[03:38.24]We don’t dance alone\n[03:39.84]We still dance when the night gets heavy\n[03:43.12]Still sing when the sky turns gray\n[03:45.44]Hands up if your heart stays ready\n[03:47.44]Love don’t break, we find a way\n[0